    {
      "id": "SFPL",
      "code_hash": "f775b7173aa80cf91dfb49ad309023a6",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"2-the-key-insight-attention-is-consistent\">2 \u00b7 The Key Insight: Attention Is Consistent</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">SnapKV is built on one empirical observation: <strong>attention heads are consistent</strong>.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">When generating token <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(t||)</marimo-tex>, the attention pattern over the prompt looks almost\nidentical to the pattern at token <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(t+1||)</marimo-tex>, <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(t+2||)</marimo-tex>, ... The model \"decides\" which\nprompt tokens matter during the <strong>prefill stage</strong> and sticks to that decision.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">This means we can look at the last few tokens of the prompt (the <strong>observation\nwindow</strong>) and use their attention patterns to predict which KV entries will be\nneeded during generation \u2014 <em>before generation even starts</em>.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
